author: Times Sports Staff
title: AREA COLLEGES: Herons field hockey wins fourth straight
text:
AREA COLLEGES: Herons field hockey wins fourth straight Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
GENEVA — The sixth-ranked William Smith field hockey team kept rolling with a weekend sweep. 
The Herons, who started the weekend on the road with a 3-2 Liberty League win over Union Friday, shut out Cortland 3-0 in a non-conference battle at McCooey Field. 
William Smith (13-1, 3-1) has now won four consecutive games. 
Alessandra Patrizio netted her 19th goal of the season 54 seconds into the game against Cortland. Hannah Wood raised her season total to 22 with a pair of scores. 
Cydney Conley and Maura Moran both assisted on Wood’s last goal. Goalie Emily King made three saves. 
Patrizio hit the net twice and assisted on Wood’s game-winning goal in the 65th minute Friday. 
Biz Chirco (2 saves) and King both saw time in goal. 
Brockport 4, Keuka 1 
BROCKPORT — Ashley D’Amore scored the lone goal for Keuka (2-10). Elizabeth Sherman stopped 17 shots in the cage. 
CROSS COUNTRY 
CCOC Championships 
GENEVA — The Herons claimed second at the 11th annual event at Seneca Lake State Park. Freshman Eva Gurian finished fourth (19:44.9) out of 121 runners. 
The Statesmen took fifth as team. Tyler Sutherland was eighth (27:30.9) out of 125 runners.
